dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Hungerford, drift, sheet 267
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 267 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 51.516700. South Decimal Degree 51.3500. East Decimal Degree -1.2500. West Decimal Degree -1.6500. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of England. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original Geological Survey on the one-inch scale by W. T. Aveline, et al. Published on sheets 12, 13, 14 & 34 Old Series 1857-60. Resurveyed on the six-inch scale by F. J. Bennett. Published, with Drift, Nov. 1898.".
